<TITLE> 1 hurt as Oil-Gas Committee attacked </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 22 (bdnews24.com)  One person was seriously injured as a procession of the National Committee for the Protection of Oil, Gas, and Mineral Resources, and Power and Ports was attacked. The procession of the citizens' platform, demanding an end to power and water crisis, was attacked in front of the Dhaka College at around 5.30pm on Wednesday. Engineer Sheikh Muhammad Shahidullah, convener of the committee, told bdnews24.com about 70 people joined the procession. The Oil Gas Protection Committee, as it is popularly called, marched in protest against the utilities crisis and the undue benefits given to foreign oil and gas companies. Some 70 people joined the procession starting at Shahbagh and scheduled to end at New Market. Shahidulllah claimed that a group of 20 to 25 people attacked the procession when they were just about to cross Dhaka College. They smashed the megaphone that was being used to shout slogans and attacked the procession injuring a few of the marchers. The one marcher seriously injured could not be identified immediately. The convener said that the attackers might have been activists of a students' association. Md Anis, a sub-inspector of the New Market Police Station said that no such incident had occurred. b
